If the actual change of $\textbf{P}\cdot\hat{\textbf{n}}$ with $E_b$ would be solely due to a change in $\eta$, then $\tau_{\textsc{ews}}\approx 0$ since $g\approx 0$ for constructive interference \cite{SOM}, but such an infinitesimal time-delay would be in conflict with the attosecond time-resolved photoemission literature \cite{Cavalieri:2007, Eckle:2008, Pazourek:2013, Lucchini:2015, Kling:2008, Locher:2015}.\\


